OL,3,CPatients left in hospital corridors
OL,4,Cfor 'dangerously long periods',
OL,5,Cexperts warn
OL,7,FPatients are referred to AMUs by
OL,8,Femergency department (A&E) doctors,
OL,9,Fother hospital departments, or
OL,10,Fdirectly by a GP.
OL,12,FThe latest Society for Acute Medicine
OL,13,Fbenchmarking audit, carried out in
OL,14,FJune, included more than 10,000
OL,15,Fpatients.
OL,17,FIt found nearly half were initially
OL,18,Fseen in emergency departments rather
OL,19,Fthan AMUs, and over nine in 10 spent
OL,20,Fmore than four hours waiting in A&E.
