OL,3,CPatients left in hospital corridors
OL,4,Cfor 'dangerously long periods',
OL,5,Cexperts warn
OL,7,FMore than half of patients waited
OL,8,Fmore than 12 hours in emergency
OL,9,Fdepartments, with older and frailer
OL,10,Fpatients most likely to wait this long.
OL,12,FAccording to the SAM, a lack of beds
OL,13,Fin AMUs and on hospital wards means
OL,14,Fpatients are left for "dangerously
OL,15,Flong periods" on corridors.
OL,17,FIt said AMUs receive the majority of
OL,18,Fpatients admitted to hospital from
OL,19,FA&E, helping to maintain the flow of
OL,20,Fpatients, so blockages have a big
OL,21,Fknock-on effect.
