OL,3,CPatients left in hospital corridors
OL,4,Cfor 'dangerously long periods',
OL,5,Cexperts warn
OL,7,FSAM's new president, Dr Vicky Price,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Corridor care is causing harm
OL,9,Ffor patients on a daily basis.
OL,11,F"It is associated with increased
OL,12,Flength of stay and increased
OL,13,Fmortality, and patients should be
OL,14,Fflowing through AMUs.
OL,16,F"The evidence shows that patients have
OL,17,Fbetter outcomes when they come through
OL,18,Facute medical units ` lower mortality,
OL,19,Fshorter stays and better patient
OL,20,Fexperience ` so we must fix this
OL,21,Fsituation."
